x4freetext: 12C ions beam, incident energy from 57.2 to 72.7 MeV
The targets with about 200-500 ug/cm2 in thickness.
The C-12 ions of 25 degree were detected by
Mica track detector, the angle were from
70 to 170 degree between it and incident beam, and
the distance was 10 cm between it and the target.
The fission cross sections were normalized by assuming
Coulomb scattering for 12C detected at 25 deg.
Total uncertainty of fission cross section
Separation of elastic scattering from inelastic
